          <!-- Slide 3: Agent Collaborators -->
          <section class="slide" id="deck-slide-3">
            <div class="slide-content">
              <h2 class="slide-title">Agent Collaborators</h2>
              <p class="slide-desc">Fabric supports teams of humans working with teams of agents. Both are treated as actors in the system, enabling dynamic, self-directed collaboration instead of rigid, hard-coded orchestration graphs.</p>
              <ul class="slide-bullets">
                <li><strong>Actor Interaction:</strong> Both humans and agents can query, message, or inspect Agents.</li>
                <li><strong>Self-Directed Management:</strong> Agents are equipped with access to the <code>fabric</code> CLI, letting agents themselves dynamically spawn, query, or stop sub-agents.</li>
                <li><strong>Asynchronous Messaging:</strong> Collaborators communicate asynchronously, sending messages and delegating work across safe, pluggable brokers.</li>
                <li><strong>Interactive Inspection:</strong> Humans and parent agents can attach or "look" at running agent processes (via <code>tmux</code>) or view logs.</li>
              </ul>
