          <!-- Slide 4: Agent Notifications -->
          <section class="slide" id="deck-slide-4">
            <div class="slide-content">
              <h2 class="slide-title">Agent Notifications</h2>
              <p class="slide-desc">Fabric combines state and messages into notifications to provide robust asynchronous event driven orchestration patterns.</p>
              <ul class="slide-bullets">
                <li><strong>State &amp; Message Intersection:</strong> Notifications represent events triggered when an agent transitions state (e.g. from <code>working</code> to <code>waiting_for_input</code>).</li>
                <li><strong>Sub-Agent Suspend Pattern:</strong> When an agent delegates a task, it invokes a child, updates its activity to <code>blocked</code>, and sleeps. No active polling occurs.</li>
                <li><strong>Event-Driven Wakeup:</strong> Once the sub-agent completes, stalls, or needs input, a notification hook automatically wakes the parent agent up.</li>
                <li><strong>Human Attention Alerts:</strong> Triggers notifications to Slack, terminals, or dashboards the instant an agent gets stuck or requires human confirmation.</li>
              </ul>
